00:00:39.300 --> 00:00:45.150
The Mozart Effect; the Mozart Effect is one
of the most popular scientific concepts surrounding

00:00:45.150 --> 00:00:46.150
music.

00:00:46.150 --> 00:00:51.360
It was developed by Dr. Gordon Shaw a few
decades ago, and the premise is simple; classical

00:00:51.360 --> 00:00:53.219
music makes you smarter.

00:00:53.219 --> 00:00:58.140
In his research, he claimed that listening
to classical music can raise your IQ by up

00:00:58.140 --> 00:00:59.480
to 9 points.

00:00:59.480 --> 00:01:03.960
The main basis for this line of thought has
to do with spatial reasoning.

00:01:03.960 --> 00:01:09.030
This type of brain activity is used in math,
chess, engineering and science.

00:01:09.030 --> 00:01:13.560
According to the Mozart Effect, classical
music boosts spatial reasoning considerably.

00:01:13.560 --> 00:01:18.149
Maybe it's time to start playing some Mozart
while we study.

00:01:18.149 --> 00:01:21.080
Music therapy helps repair brain damage.

00:01:21.080 --> 00:01:25.470
Brain damage is one of the most discussed
topics in the world of psychology.

00:01:25.470 --> 00:01:29.820
Some people suffering from brain damage go
through tremendous pain and discomfort, and

00:01:29.820 --> 00:01:32.040
their life is seriously impacted.

00:01:32.040 --> 00:01:33.750
But what if music could help?

00:01:33.750 --> 00:01:38.619
New research shows that music can actually
repair brain damage, and it's been hypothesized

00:01:38.619 --> 00:01:43.580
that music therapy could be responsible for
neurogenesis, which is the birth of new brain

00:01:43.580 --> 00:01:45.040
cells.

00:01:45.040 --> 00:01:48.100
Hearing music in your dreams is incredibly
rare.

00:01:48.100 --> 00:01:53.080
Think about every dream you've ever had, can
you remember hearing music in a single dream?

00:01:53.080 --> 00:01:57.920
If you're like the vast majority of the population,
you've probably never heard so much as a jingle

00:01:57.920 --> 00:01:59.330
in your dreams.

00:01:59.330 --> 00:02:05.450
According to a 2018 study, only 6% of all
remembered dreams include music.

00:02:05.450 --> 00:02:09.890
Unsurprisingly, you're much more likely to
hear music in your dreams if you're a musician

00:02:09.890 --> 00:02:12.330
or someone who listens to a lot of music.

00:02:12.330 --> 00:02:16.090
But even then, the number is still very low.

00:02:16.090 --> 00:02:19.540
Your entire brain is activated when you listen
to music.

00:02:19.540 --> 00:02:23.810
There aren't many activities that make your
whole brain light up, but listening to music

00:02:23.810 --> 00:02:25.670
is definitely one of them.

00:02:25.670 --> 00:02:30.030
When you listen to music, there's not a single
part of your brain that isn't activated.

00:02:30.030 --> 00:02:34.710
Parts of the brain that are responsible for
emotions, creativity and even motor functions

00:02:34.710 --> 00:02:37.030
are working while listening to music.

00:02:37.030 --> 00:02:41.670
So if you're looking for a full brain workout,
simply put on your favorite song.

00:02:41.670 --> 00:02:43.360
Music can improve language proficiency.

00:02:43.360 --> 00:02:48.440
The relationship between language and music
is one of the most fascinating things in the

00:02:48.440 --> 00:02:50.080
world of psychology.

00:02:50.080 --> 00:02:54.390
To put it simply, these two things are very
closely linked to one another.

00:02:54.390 --> 00:03:00.050
A 2012 study pointed out that despite what
previous research suggested, music and language

00:03:00.050 --> 00:03:02.490
are not separate functions in the brain.

00:03:02.490 --> 00:03:06.850
Traditionally, speech functions were thought
to exist in the left hemisphere of the brain

00:03:06.850 --> 00:03:09.740
while music functions existed in the right
hemisphere.

00:03:09.740 --> 00:03:14.950
But today, it's widely accepted that both
hemispheres are responsible for music and

00:03:14.950 --> 00:03:15.950
speech.

00:03:15.950 --> 00:03:20.140
What this means is that music functions can
actually improve speech functions and vice

00:03:20.140 --> 00:03:21.150
versa.

00:03:21.150 --> 00:03:25.340
In a sense, both activities are working the
same muscle.

